02:06.993 --> 02:09.426
May l have a word with you, please?

02:19.405 --> 02:21.430
Look, the name is Benjamin Siegel.

02:21.641 --> 02:24.576
Benjamin. Benjamin.
lt's in the Bible.

02:24.777 --> 02:26.574
lt's also on my birth certificate.

02:26.779 --> 02:29.771
Now, ''bug'' is a name
for something that crawls in dirt.

02:30.283 --> 02:32.774
l couldn't agree with you more.
You're absolutely right.

02:32.986 --> 02:34.214
No question, Mr. Siegel.

02:34.854 --> 02:36.481
-Ben.
-Ben.

02:36.689 --> 02:39.783
l know you're here with your family.
l don't wanna embarrass you.

02:39.993 --> 02:42.120
l appreciate that deeply.

02:44.464 --> 02:47.228
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye to you, Mr. Siegel.

02:47.433 --> 02:49.401
And thank you again.

03:15.562 --> 03:21.899
-Mr. Siegel. Floor please, madam?
-Penthouse.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.611
lf we make love,
it'll be the only time.

03:33.846 --> 03:36.906
-What if you like it?
-l know l'll like it.

03:38.218 --> 03:42.450
-l think l got off on the wrong floor.
-You'd better get back on.

03:58.438 --> 04:02.340
-Don't stop.
-ls that hurting?

04:06.946 --> 04:08.277
Meyer, take it easy.

04:08.481 --> 04:11.575
l'm gonna be a half an hour.
l got 1 0 minutes of sunlamp....

04:11.784 --> 04:15.117
All right,
l'll do the sunlamp on the train.

04:15.321 --> 04:20.156
Of course l'm alone.
She was an hour ago.

04:20.360 --> 04:22.794
l have thought about it.
l gotta do it.

04:22.996 --> 04:26.591
Call Charlie. He likes to take a nap
when there's gonna be trouble.

04:34.741 --> 04:36.174
Ben, l gotta tell you again...

04:36.376 --> 04:39.937
...that it really does affect my opinion
of your ability to administrate...

04:40.146 --> 04:42.444
...when you get involved
in this type of detail.

04:42.649 --> 04:44.776
Charlie, tell him what you said
when l told you.

04:44.984 --> 04:48.681
-What do you think l said to you?
-See what l'm talking about?

04:48.888 --> 04:52.790
-Then you just shook your head.
-Of course. What else was l gonna do?

04:57.930 --> 05:00.262
All right. Count to 53.

05:11.411 --> 05:13.902
-Good evening, Mr. Siegel.
-Hi.

05:14.814 --> 05:17.180
-Give that a brush for me, will you?
-Sure.

05:19.185 --> 05:21.380
Hiya, Marty. Same to you, Ted.

05:23.923 --> 05:25.117
Hiya, Jerry.

05:25.325 --> 05:28.488
Ben. What are you doing here?
l thought you were going to California.

05:28.695 --> 05:30.822
l am. l just came
to give you a goodbye present.

05:32.365 --> 05:34.663
-Present?
-Yeah, open it.

05:41.574 --> 05:43.064
-l don't get it.
-You know...

05:43.276 --> 05:45.642
...Meyer, Charlie and l,
we hire you to do a job...

05:45.845 --> 05:48.746
...we pay you a nice salary,
we throw in a piece of the action...

05:48.948 --> 05:51.746
...and you pay us back by
stealing from us for the second time.

05:51.951 --> 05:54.283
-Stealing?
-Yeah. The shirt off my back.

05:54.487 --> 05:58.685
Do you want the shirt off my back?
l'd be happy to give it to you. Here.

05:58.891 --> 06:02.190
-From Sulka's. The ones l wear.
-Could l say something here?

06:02.395 --> 06:04.420
lf l had taken longer,
l would've bought you...

06:04.630 --> 06:07.497
...some pants and suits and jackets
and shoes. But you know what?

06:07.700 --> 06:10.601
-But l can give you a couple of tips.
-Tips?

06:10.803 --> 06:14.000
-Let me see your shoes.
-My shoes?

06:14.207 --> 06:17.233
l don't wanna be rude to you,
but they don't go with anything.

06:17.677 --> 06:20.111
-Another couple tips....
-l'm a little confused here.

06:22.281 --> 06:25.944
Thirty-nine hundred dollars we pay
to hire three guys to take care of this.

06:26.152 --> 06:27.483
What are we doing here?

06:27.687 --> 06:31.088
What am l gonna tell you, Charlie,
his thinking process?

06:31.491 --> 06:34.426
The way l see it,
Ben has only one problem...

06:34.627 --> 06:38.927
...the same problem he's had since
we were kids together on the street:

06:39.132 --> 06:40.622
He doesn't respect money.

06:47.707 --> 06:53.009
But that's for summer, and, Jerry,
you don't have to worry about summer.

06:53.212 --> 06:54.736
Ben, no, don't.

06:54.947 --> 06:58.815
lf it was just business, l'd be selling
insurance or importing dresses.

07:19.071 --> 07:20.732
Remember this, Ben:

07:20.940 --> 07:24.671
The key to taking over Jack Dragna's
Southern California rackets...

07:24.877 --> 07:26.708
...is to come in smooth.

07:26.913 --> 07:30.508
Approach him like all we want
is to come in as a partner.

07:30.716 --> 07:35.244
The guy's been running the rackets
for 20 years with no competition.

07:35.488 --> 07:37.888
Except for Mickey Cohen,
who don't even count.

07:38.090 --> 07:41.355
So the only way to move in
on Dragna is amiably.

07:41.561 --> 07:43.324
What about the gambling joints
and clubs?

07:43.529 --> 07:45.793
-Vito, l just said it's fifty-fifty.
-Fifty-fifty.

07:45.998 --> 07:49.593
We move in, but we don't
ruin anything by being too crazy.

07:49.802 --> 07:53.499
Joey A. knows Jack Dragna
personally. What do you think, Joey?

07:54.006 --> 07:58.067
Jack's a cold-blooded killer,
so you gotta be careful with him.

07:58.277 --> 08:01.212
Just don't say nothing
that he'd take offense at.

08:01.848 --> 08:05.079
-What are you smiling at?
-Nothing.

08:07.186 --> 08:11.589
-Why can't we go to California?
-Maybe next time.

08:13.226 --> 08:14.557
What is it?

08:14.760 --> 08:18.025
Ben, when you get to Los Angeles,
don't call George.

08:18.231 --> 08:21.530
l know he's a good friend of yours,
but he's such a movie star now...

08:21.734 --> 08:24.464
...he attracts more attention
than Franklin Delano Roosevelt.

08:24.704 --> 08:28.640
-The trip's gotta be quick and quiet.
-And amiable.

08:28.875 --> 08:31.173
Very funny. Twelve days.

08:31.377 --> 08:34.938
Four days out. Four days
of diplomacy. Four days back.

08:35.147 --> 08:37.910
-No one even knows you were there.
-All right.

08:40.720 --> 08:44.315
Ben, could l talk to you
for a minute, alone?

08:44.524 --> 08:47.425
After l say goodbye to the family,
all right?

08:52.732 --> 08:54.996
-l'll miss you.
-l'll miss you.

08:55.201 --> 09:00.002
When l get you on the phone,
tell me what presents you want.

09:00.239 --> 09:04.471
-l already know what l want.
-Don't tell me now. Think about it.

09:06.412 --> 09:08.107
<i>I need money, Ben.</i>

09:08.681 --> 09:10.979
-How much?
-Fifty thousand dollars.

09:11.183 --> 09:12.377
For what?

09:12.585 --> 09:17.852
The cops, the DA, the FBl.
They're threatening to lock me up.

09:18.057 --> 09:22.551
They're no good, these people,
except Assistant DA Allen Stein.

09:22.762 --> 09:25.822
Jewish kid. Nice fella.
His family's from Bedford Street.

09:26.032 --> 09:27.932
What happened to the 50,000
l just gave you?

09:28.134 --> 09:30.659
-What 50,000?
-For the armored-truck heist.

09:30.870 --> 09:33.839
That 50,000?
That 50,000's gone, Ben.

09:34.040 --> 09:37.100
You know me with money,
l blew it at the track.

09:37.710 --> 09:40.645
Harry, what are you saying?

09:40.846 --> 09:44.543
That if l don't give you $50,000,
you'll rat on everyone, including me?

09:44.750 --> 09:50.347
You? Never. l love you, Ben.
l would never rat on you. Never.

09:53.359 --> 09:55.589
You ain't gonna kill me, Ben,
are you?

10:02.768 --> 10:06.898
l'm gonna try very hard
to forget that this ever happened.

10:07.173 --> 10:10.404
-l owe you my life, Ben.
-l'd say that's a fair assessment.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.475
God bless you, Ben.

10:12.678 --> 10:16.114
-Bend your knees, Harry.
-Bend my knees?

10:16.315 --> 10:20.081
When you jump from the train,
bend your knees to soften the impact.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.015
Bend my knees.

10:22.221 --> 10:25.554
Okay, Ben. Sure thing.

10:45.344 --> 10:47.107
-Are you who l think you are?
-Yes, l am.

10:47.313 --> 10:49.076
-Your autograph, please?
-All right.

10:50.449 --> 10:53.247
Ray? Okay. ''To Ray.''
Here you go, Ray.

10:53.452 --> 10:55.181
Okay, we'll get everybody here.

10:57.490 --> 11:00.391
This has been four of the most
wonderful days l've ever spent.

11:00.593 --> 11:05.690
l gotta tell you, a lot of it
was in the motion of the train.

11:06.365 --> 11:08.060
-Ben.
-Hey.

11:09.035 --> 11:10.366
Oh, my gosh.

11:10.569 --> 11:14.369
Mister, he knows you.
Are you somebody too?

11:14.907 --> 11:16.636
l love you, George.

11:16.842 --> 11:19.174
You're looking great,
like a million bucks.

11:19.378 --> 11:23.144
You're looking good yourself, Georgie.
Very dapper, very dapper.

11:23.349 --> 11:27.911
Well, that's what they pay me for.
Okay, we're moving on here.

11:28.254 --> 11:32.520
l've got you registered at the
Beverly Hills Hotel, bungalow five.

11:32.725 --> 11:36.388
l know you said four days,
but l reserved six.

11:39.999 --> 11:43.696
But Jack Dragna's the kingpin here?
What do you hear about him?

11:43.903 --> 11:46.599
From what l hear,
he runs a nice little operation.

11:47.106 --> 11:51.167
You've got a city with 3 million people
and his operation is nice and little?

11:51.377 --> 11:55.711
l don't know. Less to worry about.
l'll drop you off, then go to the studio.

11:55.915 --> 11:59.578
-Why don't l go over with you?
-All right. lf you like.

12:10.529 --> 12:13.657
-Georgie, who are they?
-Bit players.

12:13.866 --> 12:16.835
l'm gonna run to Makeup.
Meet me on stage 2 1 .

12:42.361 --> 12:46.229
Enjoying yourself?
Now take a walk. Out.

12:46.699 --> 12:48.667
When l call for the extras,
then they come in.

12:48.868 --> 12:51.564
Do not come in before l call for you,
understand?

12:51.771 --> 12:53.932
Now, you wanna get outside
with them?

12:54.406 --> 12:56.340
You having a hard time
understanding me?

12:56.542 --> 13:01.104
When l need extras, l'll call for them.
Until then, wait outside.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.078
l'm not getting through, am l?

13:04.250 --> 13:08.380
Want me to send you to Wardrobe?
They take the suit, you're out of here.

13:09.021 --> 13:10.818
You want me to get tough with you?

13:11.157 --> 13:13.853
lf l have to, l will.
l will throw you out if l have to.

13:14.059 --> 13:17.119
You want me to pick you up
and throw you out? You think l can't?

13:17.329 --> 13:19.456
l don't need this aggravation
this time of day--

13:19.665 --> 13:21.360
Tim.

13:21.567 --> 13:23.535
This is my friend from New York,
Benny Siegel.

13:23.736 --> 13:26.296
He'll be spending the day with me.

13:34.713 --> 13:38.376
Yeah. Didn't-- Didn't--

13:38.584 --> 13:41.212
Yeah, l didn't connect....

13:41.687 --> 13:43.154
Confusion.

13:46.125 --> 13:47.558
-l'm sorry.
-lt's all right.

13:49.295 --> 13:52.822
lf you get tough with a guy,
stick to it.

13:53.766 --> 13:56.701
That's great advice. Thank you.

13:58.204 --> 14:00.297
Hank ain't very bright,
but he's my friend.

14:00.506 --> 14:03.839
lf he's hooked with a dame like you,
he'll get a lot of headaches.

14:04.043 --> 14:08.002
-l'm on to your racket.
-You've got the blueprints all drawn.

14:08.214 --> 14:10.876
-Cigarette. New cigarette.
-She's eaten a whole cigarette.

14:11.083 --> 14:12.573
Scene 36, take two. Marker.

14:12.785 --> 14:15.185
l'm telling you straight,
forget you ever seen him.

14:15.387 --> 14:17.787
lf you don't get what l mean,
this'll give you an idea.

14:17.990 --> 14:21.585
Take that money
and buy yourself some manners.

14:21.861 --> 14:23.761
For what? To waste on you?

14:24.163 --> 14:25.687
Marker.

14:25.898 --> 14:29.231
Two bucks? For what? One beer
and some phony champagne?

14:29.435 --> 14:31.426
-That's right, friend.
-Here's half a buck.

14:31.637 --> 14:34.435
-Split it between you.
-Take five. Marker.

14:35.107 --> 14:38.270
Two bucks? For what? One beer
and some phony champagne?

14:38.477 --> 14:41.002
Here's half a buck.
Split it between you.

14:41.213 --> 14:43.738
You're so cheap you're wholesale.

14:44.984 --> 14:48.385
Don't forget, mister,
l asked you nice.

14:48.587 --> 14:50.555
-Marker.
-Here we go. Rolling. Quiet, please.

14:52.191 --> 14:54.318
Reset. Reset. Let's go.

14:54.526 --> 14:56.619
Benny, you wanna hit somebody
with a chair?

14:59.999 --> 15:02.092
<i>Manpower</i>.
Scene 38, take eight. Marker.

15:03.202 --> 15:06.069
Boy, with this,
l can hit home runs all night.

15:08.307 --> 15:10.298
Here. Take this,
in case l wanna come back.

15:11.343 --> 15:14.039
l feel like l should say something.
Can't l have a line?

15:14.246 --> 15:17.079
Honey, he's the star. Let's go.

15:21.320 --> 15:24.414
That was pretty impressive,
Georgie boy.

15:25.057 --> 15:28.322
-Well, Benny, l'm a pro.
-Sure.

15:32.031 --> 15:33.589
May l?

15:34.733 --> 15:38.362
lf you want a simple yes or no,
you'll have to finish the question.

15:38.570 --> 15:41.937
-Light your cigarette?
-Sure.

15:50.149 --> 15:54.108
The way you were staring, l thought
you'd ask for something more exciting.

15:54.320 --> 15:57.255
-Like what?
-Use your imagination.

15:58.090 --> 16:02.754
-l'm using it.
-Let me know when you're finished.

16:12.137 --> 16:15.004
Now you're gonna tell me
she's a bit player?

16:15.207 --> 16:18.108
Flamingo? Not for Joey Adonis.
That's Virginia Hill.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.105
Yeah? That's Flamingo, huh?

16:21.580 --> 16:24.515
Now, don't get no ideas, Ben.
You know how crazy Joey is.

16:24.717 --> 16:27.447
No woman's worth a bullet
between the eyes. Am l right?

16:27.653 --> 16:30.144
lt depends on whose eyes
and which woman.

16:35.127 --> 16:38.460
Look, you're Ben Siegel
and l'm Virginia Hill, okay?

16:38.664 --> 16:41.656
Why are you so interested in a gal
who's going with your friend?

16:41.867 --> 16:43.664
What friend? Joey A.?
He's not my friend.

16:43.869 --> 16:46.770
He's an associate of an associate.
Are you still going with him?

16:46.972 --> 16:49.304
lf it were New Year's Eve,
he would be my date.

16:49.508 --> 16:51.476
Who would your date be?

16:51.677 --> 16:53.304
-Wife.
-Wife?

16:53.512 --> 16:55.104
-Esta.
-Esther?

16:55.314 --> 16:56.906
Esta. E-S-T-A.

16:57.116 --> 17:02.452
Good. l'll bet Esta lives her life
faithful to her one and only Ben...

17:02.688 --> 17:06.714
...who plays around like a jackrabbit
and lies about it through his teeth.

17:06.925 --> 17:08.449
l don't lie to Esta.

17:08.660 --> 17:12.528
That's noble. What do you do,
confess your sins three times a day?

17:15.601 --> 17:19.162
Now, what exactly does Mr. Esta
want from Miss Virginia?

17:20.138 --> 17:23.939
Right now? Mr. Esta is having
a tremendous amount of difficulty...

17:24.143 --> 17:26.667
...imagining anything
he doesn't want from Miss Virginia.

17:27.146 --> 17:30.582
-Are you ready for a divorce?
-Never.

17:30.783 --> 17:35.220
My, oh, my. You're pretty ferocious
where Mom's concerned, aren't you?

17:35.921 --> 17:40.255
The rest of the time, you're another
sweet-talking, fuck-happy fellow...

17:40.459 --> 17:44.395
...with nothing to offer but dialogue.
Dialogue's cheap in Hollywood.

17:45.030 --> 17:48.830
Why don't you run outside
and jerk yourself a soda?

18:02.748 --> 18:08.345
Let me ask you, how would someone
go about getting a screen test done?

18:08.554 --> 18:11.921
-You know someone who wants one?
-No, no, no. l just....

18:12.124 --> 18:15.252
l just thought if it came up
in a conversation....

18:15.461 --> 18:18.225
What about Virginia Hill?
Does she have a future in movies?

18:18.430 --> 18:21.888
ln movies? l don't know
if l've got a future in movies.

18:22.101 --> 18:23.295
Lana Turner lives there.

18:24.203 --> 18:26.467
Cesar Romero lives there.

18:28.707 --> 18:31.175
And Gary Cooper is in
that house on the right.

18:31.376 --> 18:33.071
He paid 45 grand.

18:33.278 --> 18:37.009
-Houses bring in that kind of money?
-Sure, and more.

18:37.216 --> 18:40.583
-Whose is that?
-Lawrence.... The opera singer.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.845
-Melchoir?
-No, no, no. The other guy.

18:43.055 --> 18:45.285
-What other guy?
-What's-his-name.

18:45.891 --> 18:47.984
-Tibbett? Lawrence Tibbett? Stop.
-That's it.

18:49.394 --> 18:52.659
-What are you doing?
-Paying my respects.

19:02.040 --> 19:04.304
-Yes?
-l'm looking for Mr. Lawrence Tibbett.

19:04.610 --> 19:05.941
Mr. Tibbett's in the study.

19:06.445 --> 19:08.276
-May l tell him who's calling?
-Ben Siegel.

19:08.480 --> 19:10.778
-ls he expecting you?
-Not unless he's psychic.

19:12.651 --> 19:17.486
Well, would you excuse me
for a moment, please.

19:23.061 --> 19:28.727
-How far is your house from here?
-Half a mile. What are you doing?

19:33.839 --> 19:35.864
Mr. Siegel.

19:36.775 --> 19:41.007
Lawrence Tibbett. You have no idea
what an honor it is to meet you.

19:41.213 --> 19:46.344
l took my family to hear you sing
<i>Rigoletto</i> at the Met last year.

19:46.552 --> 19:48.645
lt was one of the great evenings
of our lives.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.754
Well, you overwhelm me,
Mr. Siegel.

19:50.956 --> 19:52.651
-Ben.
-Ben?

19:52.858 --> 19:55.656
-That's beautiful.
-Ben Siegel?

19:55.861 --> 19:59.388
You wouldn't be related
to Bugsy Siegel, would you?

19:59.598 --> 20:02.726
-''Bugsy''? What do you mean?
-l beg your pardon.

20:02.935 --> 20:05.870
A bug is nothing. A bug doesn't exist.
The word has no meaning.

20:06.071 --> 20:08.539
lt's used out of ignorance.
Do you know what a bug is?

20:08.740 --> 20:11.072
A bug is a colloquialism.
lt has no basis in reality.

20:11.276 --> 20:13.608
lnsects include a wide variety
of living creatures.

20:13.812 --> 20:15.609
They fly, they crawl,
they do many things.

20:15.814 --> 20:18.180
None of them can be called a bug!
You following me?

20:18.383 --> 20:22.217
Yes. Yes, l am. l certainly didn't
mean any offense, Mr. Siegel.

20:22.421 --> 20:23.683
-Ben.
-Ben.

20:23.889 --> 20:26.983
-Mind if l look around, Larry?
-Of course. Be my guest.

20:27.192 --> 20:32.858
-Do you mind if l call you Larry?
-Not a bit. All my friends call me Larry.

20:33.065 --> 20:36.034
What brings you
to Los Angeles, Ben?

20:36.235 --> 20:37.930
Curiosity.

20:38.136 --> 20:40.934
-This is a wonderful house.
-Thank you.

20:41.139 --> 20:43.198
