01:07:12.461 --> 01:07:15.157
Before we get to what's important,
l gotta tell you guys...

01:07:15.364 --> 01:07:17.855
...l got rid of that seedy canker sore
in Las Vegas.

01:07:18.067 --> 01:07:21.901
That's why we came. You had
no right to give that casino up.

01:07:22.104 --> 01:07:26.234
-Casino? lt was an outhouse.
-You should have consulted us.

01:07:26.709 --> 01:07:30.008
-That's the arrangement we got.
-l got no arrangement with you, Vito.

01:07:30.212 --> 01:07:32.180
l have an arrangement
with Meyer and Charlie.

01:07:32.381 --> 01:07:36.181
But don't worry. When l tell you
what l'm gonna build in its place...

01:07:36.385 --> 01:07:39.548
...you'll understand for the first time
the meaning of ''transcendent.''

01:07:39.755 --> 01:07:41.313
Tell us now.

01:07:42.925 --> 01:07:49.125
Meyer, l have found the answer
to the dreams of America.

01:07:49.331 --> 01:07:52.858
You wanna be a little more specific?

01:07:53.069 --> 01:07:55.537
-The Flamingo.
-A bird?

01:07:55.738 --> 01:07:59.299
What do people fantasize about?
Sex, romance, money, adventure.

01:07:59.508 --> 01:08:02.568
-l'm building a monument to them.
-Are you talking about a whorehouse?

01:08:02.778 --> 01:08:05.713
l'm talking about a hotel.
l'm talking about Las Vegas, Nevada.

01:08:05.915 --> 01:08:08.713
A place where gambling is allowed.
Where everything is allowed.

01:08:08.918 --> 01:08:12.854
The whole territory is wide open.
A palace, an oasis, a city.

01:08:13.055 --> 01:08:15.421
When the Hoover Dam is finished...

01:08:15.624 --> 01:08:19.116
...electrical power will be available
on a massive scale in Las Vegas.

01:08:19.328 --> 01:08:23.457
The Hoover Dam and fucking
are connected how?

01:08:23.666 --> 01:08:26.635
By air-conditioning.
lt's the wave of the future.

01:08:26.836 --> 01:08:31.136
Everything will be air-cooled.
Every room 72 degrees at all times.

01:08:31.340 --> 01:08:33.934
The casino?
We'll put Monte Carlo to shame.

01:08:34.176 --> 01:08:37.703
Wall-to-wall carpeting, ltalian marble,
badminton courts, stables.

01:08:37.912 --> 01:08:41.212
We'll have a lightning-fast train
from Los Angeles to Las Vegas.

01:08:41.417 --> 01:08:45.113
Planes back and forth.
Meyer, we'll have our own airport!

01:08:45.321 --> 01:08:49.758
What Ben's saying is, it's a good place
to trap people in to take their money.

01:08:49.959 --> 01:08:53.986
-ls that what you're getting at here?
-Much more. Much more.

01:08:55.331 --> 01:08:57.595
l gotta get that.

01:08:57.800 --> 01:09:01.292
l got it! l got it! Hello.

01:09:02.203 --> 01:09:06.140
Mickey, have you got someone
across the street from her house?

01:09:06.375 --> 01:09:10.310
Call Warner Bros., call Ciro's.
Find out if anybody's seen her.

01:09:10.513 --> 01:09:14.040
Then call me back.
No, not five minutes. One minute.

01:09:19.688 --> 01:09:23.715
Sit tight. Sit tight, honey.
Let me just see how they're doing.

01:09:24.359 --> 01:09:28.990
How's it--? Oh, that looks great.
Your mother's a real artist.

01:09:29.231 --> 01:09:32.166
l'm gonna run back,
l got these guys going on this thing--

01:09:32.368 --> 01:09:36.828
The children don't have the patience
that some adults do.

01:09:37.106 --> 01:09:41.406
You finish the candles in here,
l'll finish out there. We'll be ready.

01:09:44.279 --> 01:09:46.544
Don't you move,
my little birthday girl.

01:09:46.749 --> 01:09:50.845
l don't understand this desert thing.
What are we, Bedouins?

01:09:51.053 --> 01:09:52.850
Let's concentrate on Cuba.

01:09:53.055 --> 01:09:57.355
You got legalized gambling
next to Florida. lt's like another state.

01:09:57.560 --> 01:10:02.793
But it's not another state. A foreign
country can always throw you out.

01:10:02.998 --> 01:10:06.126
Nevada is another state
and it's open.

01:10:06.335 --> 01:10:09.566
lf we do this thing right,
if we follow the hotel with schools...

01:10:09.772 --> 01:10:13.731
...and churches and synagogues,
the things that give a city backbone...

01:10:13.943 --> 01:10:15.706
...we'll be in charge
before you know it.

01:10:15.978 --> 01:10:18.572
-ln charge of what?
-The state!

01:10:18.781 --> 01:10:21.511
And if you got a state,
the country is within your reach.

01:10:21.717 --> 01:10:23.207
You planning to run for president?

01:10:23.419 --> 01:10:26.752
We can help to choose the president
if we control a state.

01:10:26.956 --> 01:10:30.585
Why be bogged down by limitations?
Open your eyes to the horizons.

01:10:30.793 --> 01:10:34.752
Where do you think the money
for this is gonna come from?

01:10:34.964 --> 01:10:37.865
Since l'm doing the work
and the partners share the success...

01:10:38.067 --> 01:10:39.762
...the money should come
from them.

01:10:39.969 --> 01:10:41.766
-''Them'' meaning who?
-''Them'' meaning you.

01:10:41.971 --> 01:10:44.371
-How much are we talking about?
-One million dollars.

01:10:44.573 --> 01:10:49.237
What about the publicity?
A place like this will cause a lot of talk.

01:10:49.445 --> 01:10:51.606
Ben's getting very famous
out in California.

01:10:51.814 --> 01:10:56.945
Famous is good for Clark Gable,
but for you it's not good.

01:10:57.186 --> 01:11:00.053
The Flamingo will make
our gambling interests legitimate.

01:11:00.256 --> 01:11:04.158
Meyer, we've known each other
since we were too young to fuck.

01:11:04.360 --> 01:11:10.321
When did l ever ask you to leap
ahead with something on faith?

01:11:10.532 --> 01:11:14.662
Never, but l'm asking you now.
Do this.

01:11:18.941 --> 01:11:23.207
Mickey, you mean to tell me l've got
you and 65 guys on my payroll...

01:11:23.412 --> 01:11:25.903
...and nobody can find Virginia?

01:11:28.284 --> 01:11:32.778
Listen. l cannot function effectively
when l'm in a state of ignorance.

01:11:33.022 --> 01:11:34.546
Find her.

01:11:39.128 --> 01:11:43.656
Hold the fort. l'm nearly finished.
What's the matter?

01:11:44.300 --> 01:11:46.962
l thought you came home
to be with me on my birthday.

01:11:47.169 --> 01:11:50.366
l did. l am spending time with you
on your birthday.

01:11:50.572 --> 01:11:52.096
l just gotta finish this meeting--

01:11:52.308 --> 01:11:57.177
-l don't want to hear you!
-Millicent! Come on, honey.

01:11:58.614 --> 01:12:02.516
We're just gonna be a minute--
Come on, honey.

01:12:02.718 --> 01:12:06.950
Millicent, open the door.
l just wanna say one thing, okay?

01:12:07.389 --> 01:12:09.482
Barbara, are you in there too?

01:12:12.061 --> 01:12:14.256
Just come on down
and l'll light the candles.

01:12:14.463 --> 01:12:17.796
l'm gonna light the candles.
l'm lighting the candles.

01:12:19.068 --> 01:12:22.731
Come on down,
l'm lighting the candles.

01:12:23.572 --> 01:12:27.838
Sorry the party got a little
out of control, but l fixed it.

01:12:28.043 --> 01:12:33.208
With Charlie in jail, l'll have to
confer with him on money decisions.

01:12:33.415 --> 01:12:38.717
But pending his approval, l'm happy
to say you've got yourself a deal.

01:12:38.921 --> 01:12:42.379
-Good. Great.
-When will you get started?

01:12:42.591 --> 01:12:45.151
When l get back from ltaly.
l'm going over in a week.

01:12:45.361 --> 01:12:47.386
That, plus however long that takes.

01:12:47.596 --> 01:12:52.397
-However long what takes?
-The assassination of Mussolini.

01:12:52.601 --> 01:12:55.866
Who's gonna
assassinate Mussolini?

01:12:58.674 --> 01:13:05.307
Come here. Look, don't fuck this up
by trying to be funny.

01:13:05.514 --> 01:13:08.711
Mussolini and Hitler are trying
to knock off every Jew on earth.

01:13:08.917 --> 01:13:11.385
lf l don't do something, who will?
A bunch of ltalians?

01:13:11.587 --> 01:13:15.751
-l can stop Mussolini.
-Leave it to the Allied Forces.

01:13:15.958 --> 01:13:19.121
You're missing the point.
The Allied Forces don't have access.

01:13:19.328 --> 01:13:21.853
-l have the access.
-You have the access?

01:13:22.064 --> 01:13:24.828
One of Mussolini's best friends
is the Count Di Frasso.

01:13:25.033 --> 01:13:28.230
The Count Di Frasso's wife
has the hots for me.

01:13:28.437 --> 01:13:33.670
She'll get me close to Mussolini,
l'll blow him halfway to Siberia.

01:13:33.876 --> 01:13:35.776
Listen to me very carefully.

01:13:36.378 --> 01:13:39.142
Don't ever repeat what you just said
to me to anybody else.

01:13:39.815 --> 01:13:43.216
-That's right, it's a secret.
-l'm saying it for a different reason.

01:13:43.419 --> 01:13:44.579
Why are you saying it?

01:13:44.787 --> 01:13:49.019
Because, at best,
any normal person you say it to...

01:13:49.224 --> 01:13:53.388
...will never take anything you say
seriously again. So nothing more.

01:13:53.595 --> 01:13:58.225
Sure, but Mussolini is a dead man.
l'll be with you in a minute.

01:13:58.434 --> 01:14:03.235
l'm gonna light the candles.
l'm lighting the candles.

01:14:04.339 --> 01:14:09.402
-Let's see what Meyer wants.
-What do you want to eat?

01:14:09.611 --> 01:14:12.944
We didn't come here to eat.
We came here to do business.

01:14:20.722 --> 01:14:25.591
Millicent? l lit the candles.

01:14:27.129 --> 01:14:32.328
-Have we finished our business?
-Sure, we shouldn't have barged in.

01:14:32.534 --> 01:14:37.028
Enjoy the party for Millicent.
We'll talk tomorrow. lt sounds good.

01:14:37.239 --> 01:14:40.106
-Take care, Ben.
-Thanks for coming by.

01:14:43.545 --> 01:14:49.177
Joey. Listen,
l'm sorry about Virginia.

01:14:49.918 --> 01:14:53.979
lf you wanna take a punch at me,
take a punch at me.

01:15:00.729 --> 01:15:03.789
We're even now. l'm sorry,
l know you were in love with her.

01:15:04.500 --> 01:15:09.130
Are you kidding? l'd never let myself
fall in love with a slut like her.

01:15:48.210 --> 01:15:50.235
Your mouth is bleeding.

01:15:52.047 --> 01:15:55.016
l tripped, l whacked it on the table.
lt's nothing.

01:15:56.752 --> 01:15:59.448
l don't think
we can go on like this, Ben.

01:16:00.656 --> 01:16:05.150
-Like what?
-Should we get a divorce?

01:16:07.563 --> 01:16:12.398
Some friends just dropped by at the
wrong time. Everything's fine now.

01:16:15.637 --> 01:16:17.468
Sit down.

01:16:21.543 --> 01:16:24.671
l'm gonna go say good night
to the girls.

